WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:11.180 --> 00:00:16.280
Hi, guys! Its DIARIES OF THE CHAMPIONSHIPS. The 2nd of august in Russia is a contradictory day.

00:00:16.380 --> 00:00:30.000
According to the ancient belief, the prophet Elijah throws ice into water this day, which means it becomes cold to swim. But 2nd of august cant go without traditional swimming in fountains, right? Dear troopers, happy holiday!

00:00:30.820 --> 00:00:41.240
Even though most athletes believe in superstitions, no time for beliefs today. First 4 medals will be given to its owners just in few hours.

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:48.240
Our team has good chances for medals in 4x100 meters freestyle relay among men.

00:00:54.780 --> 00:01:02.020
And the hopes of our fans were quite reasonable. During qualifications in the morning, our team has shown the best result.

00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:10.300
Besides, strong opponents from USA, Germany , UK didn’t make it to the final. The fans were so loud and active.

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:17.020
Our first swimmer Andrey grechin finished only 5th, and Nikita Lobintsev was not fast to pass the baton.

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:23.600
However, he finished 3rd, but the French swimmer Loran Manoudou has already overpassed him quite well.

00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:31.220
Vladimir Morozov swam its 100 meters faster than anyone, and has made the gap almost reachable.

00:01:31.380 --> 00:01:40.460
But France beat Russia at the final 100 meters, and gained a golden medal, leaving Russia with silver and Italy with bronze.

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:57.040
Our women didn’t qualify for the final in the same event among females. Australia won gold here, beating USA and Netherlands and setting the new record.

00:01:57.720 --> 00:02:09.660
7 international records were set during the 1st day. The Swedish swimmer’s record in semi-final 100 meters butterfly stroke was really brilliant.

00:02:09.980 --> 00:02:18.060
Sun Yang of China was first to win a gold medal in swimming events at the 16th FINA World Championships. The double Olympic champion won the men’s 400m freestyle final.

00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:28.920
Katie Ledecky, from USA, has become the first gold medallist among women in the same programme, and set a new record.

00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:37.260
Well, that’s the end of the first day in swimming competitions. Russia has 1 silver medal.

00:02:37.500 --> 00:02:53.480
Another 4 medal events are awaiting for us tomorrow, we also advise you to go watch the preliminaries in high diving among men and water polo quarter final among women, where Russia will be competing with Netherlands.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:03:06.940
Alex Chupin will tell you about diving finals. New day is ahead, and new victories as well. Watch KAZAN 2015 TV!

